title: DB2 Deadlocks, Lockwaits and Sortoverflows
agents: aix, linux
catalog: app/db2
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the number of deadlocks, lockwaits and sortoverflows
 per second of a DB2 database. You can configure limits for each type.
 Per default no limits are set.

 This check needs the mk_db2 plugin installed in the agent.

item:
 The DB2 instance name followed by a : and the database name, e.g. db2ilog1:REST1

inventory:
 One separate check for each database will be created.

perfdata:
 Three values: The rate per second of deadlocks, lockwaits and sortoverflows.

